item.comments: A family obligation has come up. But I got the chance to hike here a few weeks ago and saw my first barn owls! Happy Trails everyone.

Had knee surgery last week. I enjoyed hiking here previously, but IF I attempt it now, would be the "weakest link", thus rather than slow down the group, I'll need to hold off till fully recovered. Have fun!
It's a great hike with Susan, enjoy!
wish I could, need to be at work for 4:30. don't think it would allow me enough time. :(
Can't make it to Manchester in the next 1/2 hr!
This sounds very interesting. I've hiked Case several times and am looking forward to the history lesson.
Highland Park was my elementary school and I love the area
I really want to get in shape
Anyone interested in a 1, 1.5 hr. mt. bike ride at Case before the hike? I'm a beg/intermediate rider, can do some single track technical stuff. No stunts.
always love susan's hikes she gives a great commentary
I've hiked Case Mountains many times. It would be interesting to hear historical context during the hike.
I've hiked it before had a great time! Wil bring alot of bug spray....First ten t yards is the hardest
I will say maybe. I have some family in town so if I can convince them to come...then I will be there.
